OL,6,FVictim-survivors allowed to read
OL,7,Fpersonal statements
OL,9,FThe review recommends that victim-
OL,10,Fsurvivors should be able to read
OL,11,Fpersonal statements at sentencing
OL,12,Fhearings, if they wish.
OL,14,FMs Laws says being able to read such
OL,15,Fstatements out in court helps victim-
OL,16,Fsurvivors "feel engaged in the process
OL,17,Fand important", stating that
OL,18,Fpreviously they had felt "quite the
OL,19,Fopposite".
OL,21,FConsideration of re-trials
